
  /**
  *
  * @ingroup processing 
  * \defgroup vPepper vPepper
  * Removes salt and pepper noise from the event stream
  * Version:1.0
  * \author  Arren Glover arren.glover@iit.it
  * \n
  * \copyright Released under the terms of the GNU GPL v2.0
  * \section intro_sec Description
  *
  
      Removes salt and pepper noise from the event stream. If an event is the only one occured within its surrounding
        (spatialSize parameter) in a certain temporal window (temporalSize parameter), it is ignored.
    
  * \section parameters_sec Parameters     
  
  *- -- name : Specifies the stem name of ports created by the module.
  *- -- height : Number of pixels on the y-axis of the sensor.
  *- -- width : Number of pixels on the x-axis of the sensor.
  *- -- spatialSize : Size of the spatial window around the event
  *- --
            temporalSize
        : How long the filter will look for events in the past within the spatial window
  * \section inputports_sec Input Ports
  * 
  *- /vPepper/vBottle:i [vBottle]  [default carrier:tcp]: 
                Input event stream to be filtered
            
  *
  
  * \section outputports_sec Output Ports
  * 
  *- /vPepper/vBottle:o [vBottle]  [default carrier:tcp]: 
                Outputs the filtered event stream
            
  *
  
  *
  * \section services_sec Services
  * 
